+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01S4pfU8AsVGPaVsin6MeFZ2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Algorithm design (before writing tests):**\n\n**Part 1 - solveToggle:** This is a system of linear equations over GF(2) (binary field). Each button is a variable (0 or 1), each light gives one equation: XOR of buttons affecting that light = target. With 40 buttons, Gaussian elimination over GF(2) works in O(M*N) time. After finding a basis solution, enumerate free variables to minimize button count, then pick lexicographically smallest among ties.\n\n**Part 2 - solveCounter:** Same but over GF(p) for prime p. Gaussian elimination works over any field. Same optimization for minimum total and lex smallest."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":305,"cache_read_input_tokens":28428,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":305},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24046fc0-045a-4fb9-9faa-7e2e1a96920f","uuid":"9f449082-e2bb-4a7f-986a-63c9bcbdabc1"}
